-- U.K.’s Hague Welcomes Appointment of Egyptian Prime Minister
-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 2012-07-25T18:09:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/u-k-s-hague-welcomes-appointment-of-egyptian-prime-minister.html
U.K. Foreign Secretary  William Hague 
said the British government welcomed the recent appointment by
Egyptian President Mohamed Mursi of Dr. Hisham Qandil as Prime
Minister, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office said in an e-
mailed statement today.  “It is an important milestone in Egypt’s transition to
full civilian, democratic rule,” Hague said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Simpson in Toronto at 
